<item>
            <title>[HBASE-16790] Need a better way to handler user&apos;s coprocessor error</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-16790</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;User&apos;s bad coprocessor caused our hbase cluster down few times.&lt;br/&gt;
Now we are going to set hbase.coprocessor.abortonerror to false to avoid them bring down whole cluster accidentally. But this is not encourage in production since it will cause inconsistent. Do we have better ways to handle this situation?&lt;br/&gt;
Just few thoughts:&lt;br/&gt;
1. Instead of shutdown RegionServer, can we just disable the table which have  coprocessor error?&lt;br/&gt;
2. Can we give some of user privilege to add coprocessor only? We can&apos;t just set hbase.coprocessor.user.enabled=false, that will cause lots of works to operation the cluster. &lt;br/&gt;
3. Can we add another step, wait for supper user approve before hbase dynamically load the  coprocessor?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
